{
  "stem": "12494.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So next morning, around 5 o'clock, or was it 5:30?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm not sure.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Very early in the morning, 30 of us young people were ready to collect the luggage of the remaining close to 1,500 people, 1,400 and odd people.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was 17 [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I-- I should mention one-- one event which sort of interferes with this.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When we were checked into Bergen-Belsen at the beginning, we had to fill out papers for the Germans telling them where we were born, what we-- our background was, the usual type of papers, and our nationality.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And of course most of us put down whatever the truth was, and the nationality was Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were citizens of Hungary.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There were a few exceptions.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Those were the people who were from that part of Hungary which used to belong to Romania and who resented Hungary very much, because Hungary treated them so badly.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they felt they would have been treated much better by Romania, and to give their nationality as Romanian.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Turns out that in August 1944, Romania jumped off the Hitler wagon and declared war on Germany.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So on December the 2nd, we were notified that we all go to Switzerland except those who declared themselves Romanian citizens, that they would not be liberated, but they would kept in Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "This involved a number of people, which I don't know the exact number, somewhere between 20 and 40 people.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "None of them survived Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They were all-- they were all-- they all died during the ensuing months.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
